			<title>Widget Issues Evoution</title>
			<section>
					<title>Binding Applications rule</title>
					<para>
						All Bugtracker management applications of all your projects can be binded to the widget. 
						For configuring applications to bind, please refer to section <xref linkend="widgetCommonSetting" endterm="widgetCommonSettingXref" />.
					</para>
			</section>
				<section>
					<title>Overview</title>
					<para>
						This widget show the issues evolution, grouped by state, in the form of a stacked area chart.
						You can hide or show issues state by clicking on state name and icon in the legend.
					</para>
					<figure>
						<title>Example of widget Issues evolution overview
						</title>
						<mediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata align="center"
									fileref="07-Widget-IssuesEvolution-Overview.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</mediaobject>
					</figure>
					
				</section>
				<section>
					<title>Widget parameters</title>
					<figure>
						<title>Configuration of widget properties</title>
						<mediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata align="center"
									fileref="07-Widget-IssuesEvolution-Setting.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</mediaobject>
					</figure>
					<para>
						This menu allow you to :
						<itemizedlist>
							<listitem>
								<para>Modify widget title in your dashboard, by editing the "name" field
								</para>
							</listitem>
							<listitem>
								<para>Select if you want to agregate all issues version, or only a specific one.
								</para>
							</listitem>
							<listitem>
								<para>Choose the evolution period you want to see (last 7 days, last 30 days or a custom date range period)
								</para>
							</listitem>
							<listitem>
								<para>Save your modifications</para>
							</listitem>
							<listitem>
								<para>Return to dashboard, by clicking on the return button at top right.
								</para>
							</listitem>
						</itemizedlist>
					</para>
				</section>
</section>
